modules.description: Reads MessagePack values from a string buffer and returns the number of bytes read along with the decoded value. Reads multiple MessagePack values from a string buffer, returning the final position and list of messages. Writes a MessagePack value to a buffer, returning the number of bytes written. Converts a MessagePack value to its byte representation in a buffer.

Reads MessagePack values from byte buffers and writes them to output buffers, supporting both single and multiple message decoding. Operates on OCaml's Bytes.t for input and Buffer.t for output. Used to parse sequences of MessagePack-encoded data from a byte stream or serialize values into a buffer for transmission.

Reads and decodes MessagePack values from strings, returning the number of bytes read and the decoded value. Reads multiple messages from a string, returning the updated position and a list of decoded values. Writes a MessagePack value to a byte buffer and converts a MessagePack value to its byte representation.

Reads and decodes MessagePack values from byte buffers, returning the number of bytes read and the parsed value. Reads multiple messages from a buffer, tracking the position and collecting decoded values into a list. Serializes MessagePack values into byte buffers, writing them at a specified position or appending to the end.

Serializes and deserializes data structures using the MessagePack binary format. It handles OCaml types such as integers, strings, lists, and tuples. Used to efficiently encode and decode data for network communication or file storage.

Reads and decodes MessagePack values from an input buffer, returning the number of bytes read and the decoded value. Reads multiple messages from a buffer, returning the new position and a list of decoded values. Serializes a MessagePack value into an output buffer, returning the number of bytes written. Operates on custom buffer types for input and output. Used to parse streams of MessagePack-encoded data and generate serialized byte sequences for transmission or storage.
